description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for experienced Registered Nurses in Emergency care to join our Nurse bank. In return we offer an enhanced rate of pay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, highly motivated Adult Registered Nurses to work within our Department which has recently been rated outstanding for ‘well lead’ by the CQC .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an innovative and dynamic Emergency Department with excellent performance in all the quality indicators such as the 4 hour performance target and have our achievements and high quality care have been widely recognised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will enjoy a challenging, varied pace and exciting working environment caring for all emergency attendance in four areas of the department including working in our 7 bedded resus, and our Children and Young Peoples Area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The senior team will ensure a supportive and proactive working environment with robust training and education which will facilitate your career development and progression and build on your current achievements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant must:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Have well developed communication skills and time management.&lt;br /&gt;• Have effective organisational abilities.&lt;br /&gt;• Be a first level Registered Adult or Paediatric Nurse&lt;br /&gt;• Desirably have critical care skills.&lt;br /&gt;• Desirably have experience in an acute setting.&lt;br /&gt;• Desirably have FLIPS qualification or equivalent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard Clarkson - Head of Service for Emergency Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: richard.clarkson@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:  01623 622515, extn. 2792.&lt;/p&gt;
